<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-27T01:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-27T01:44:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5041/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-27T06:00:00-00:44">January
                                    27, 1943—6 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. My telegram No. 11, January 26, 10 a.m. The amendments to the bill
                            passed by the Senate yesterday have been telegraphed to Akron with the
                            request to forward them to the Department immediately. They do not alter
                            the bill materially. It will be presented to the House today where
                            amendments will unquestionably be agreed to. Barclay has 5 days in which
                            to sign but present indications are that he will do so at once.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>